verbose_text: When cultured myocytes from patients with OB/T2D (n = 5) were examined in parallel with those from the normal subjects (n = 2), the basal phosphorylation levels of PKB, p70s6K, p42 / p44 MAPKs and p90RSK1 were significantly lower (p < 0.001) in the cells from patients with OB/T2D compared to those from the normal subjects (XREF_FIG).
